</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_does_paediatric_first_aid_differ_from_adult_first_aid_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686048962" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_does_paediatric_first_aid_differ_from_adult_first_aid_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686048962 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_does_paediatric_first_aid_differ_from_adult_first_aid_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686048962 320w" width="1766" height="1179" alt="How does paediatric first aid differ from adult first aid? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="How does paediatric first aid differ from adult first aid? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" style="aspect-ratio:1766 / 1179" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-hmjpVf jFnkub pf-59_"/><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-60_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-62_">Paediatric first aid differs from adult first aid because children have unique needs and vulnerabilities. They have smaller bodies and different physiological responses and are often unable to communicate their needs or symptoms effectively. Therefore, it's crucial to have a good understanding of paediatric first aid to respond appropriately to any emergency situation involving a child.
