<br><br>Knowing how to provide basic first aid, such as CPR, choking relief, and treating wounds, can help prevent serious injuries and even save a child's life. In addition, identifying signs of illness or injury and knowing when to seek professional medical help can also make a significant difference in a child's recovery.
